Manchester United Pays Out Record Bonuses to Employees, Mail Says: Roundup

-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 
2011-09-20T10:04:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-20/manchester-united-pays-out-record-bonuses-to-employees-mail-says-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of
soccer stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the
Web.  Man. United Bonuses  Manchester United  will pay out a record of 5 million pounds
($7.9 million) in bonuses to 520 staff after winning the Premier
League and reaching the Champions League final last season, the
 Daily Mail  reported.  The non-playing staff will get a 7.9 percent bonus on their
annual salary in next month’s salary payment, the Mail said.  Hargreaves Debut  Owen Hargreaves  could make his Manchester City debut in
tomorrow’s Carling Cup game against Birmingham,  the Sun 
reported.  The former United midfielder may play for 45 minutes as
coach  Roberto Mancini  rests “five or six” first-team players,
the Sun said, citing comments by the Italian.  Barkley Offer  Chelsea is willing to offer 20 million pounds for 17-year-
old Everton midfielder Ross Barkley in the January transfer
window, the  Daily Mirror  reported.  Blues coach Andre Villas-Boas had an informal offer for the
teenager shunned in the offseason, the Mirror said.  De Rossi Bid  City’s Mancini will make a new 8 million pound bid for
Roma’s  Daniele De Rossi  in January,  the Sun  reported.  De Rossi, out of contract next year, is refusing to sign a
new deal with the Serie A team, according to the Sun.  To contact the reporters on this story:
